alysis relating to intersectional identities. Contributors explore how being older intersects with differences of ethnicity, gender, sexuality and class. Offering a critical focus and original contribution to an emerging, although still relatively neglected field, this collection extends knowledge concerning intimacies, practices and pleasures for those thought to represent normative, non-normative and 'new normative' forms of sexual identification and expression.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Gerontology.2bisacsh1 aBonhomme, Laura Scarrone, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHafford-Letchfield, Trish, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHafford-Letchfield, Trish, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHarley, Debra A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKwok, Dr Diana K., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLee, David M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPrzybylo, Ela, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRennie, Karen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReynolds, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReynolds, Paul, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRobinson, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSimpson, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSimpson, Paul, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aTetley, Josephine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTodd, Megan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWells, Christopher, econtributo